org.spf4j.reflect

Interface TypeMap<H>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ByTypeSupplier<H,RuntimeException>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CachingTypeMapWrapper, GraphTypeMap

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public interface TypeMap<H>
extends ByTypeSupplier<H,RuntimeException>
    Type to Object map. association is not 1 - 1. if we have type1 -> object that if type2 is subtype of type1, also type2 -> object this is useful for resolving: ITC_INHERITANCE_TYPE_CHECKING
    Author:
    Zoltan Farkas

      • getAll

        @Nonnull
Set<H> getAll(Type t)
        Get all Objects associated to all unrelated compatible types. for example we habe Object O of type T a subtype of T1 and T2. if this typemap contains Objects mapped to T1 and T2, those 2 objects will be returned if T1 and T2 are not related (subtypes of each other) if T1 extends T2 the obeject mapped to the most specific type is returned.
